# Go Core Rules

- Keep exported C ABI functions minimal and stable in `core/internal/ffi/`.
- Put runtime lifecycle and state transitions behind explicit start/stop/reload boundaries.
- Keep TUN lifecycle decoupled from outbound switching logic.
- Use context cancellation and structured error propagation for long-running routines.
- Avoid importing UI concerns into the core module.

## Example

```go
// GOOD: use context to stop worker safely
ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())
defer cancel()
```
